  "notes": "Proto-Maghrebi Arabic — abstract ancestor node for Moroccan, Algerian, Tunisian, Libyan, and Hassaniya Arabic. Key shared Maghrebi features: vowel reduction/deletion; ث → /t/; ذ → /d/; ق → /q/ preserved; Berber substrate reinforcing pharyngeals and emphatics.",
